1. The agent may call get_vehicles_by_type with vehicle_type set to "caminhoes" to list available truck brands for fleet procurement analysis.

2. The agent may call get_vehicles_by_type with vehicle_type set to "trucks" to list available truck brands for fleet procurement analysis.

3. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Scania" for truck-relevant brand price research.

4. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Volvo" for truck-relevant brand price research.

5. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Mercedes-Benz" for truck-relevant brand price research.

6. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "MAN" for truck-relevant brand price research.

7. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "DAF" for truck-relevant brand price research.

8. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Iveco" for truck-relevant brand price research.

9. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Ford" for Ford Cargo line truck price research.

10. The agent may call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Volkswagen" for VW Constellation/Delivery lines truck price research.

11. The agent may call get_car_brands to verify brand availability when the analyst is unsure of the exact brand name in the FIPE database.

12. The agent may present FIPE reference prices clearly labeled as reference values, not binding purchase prices.

13. The agent may retrieve pricing for multiple truck brands in sequence when the analyst requests a comparison.

14. The agent must not call get_vehicles_by_type with vehicle_type set to "carros".

15. The agent must not call get_vehicles_by_type with vehicle_type set to "cars".

16. The agent must not call get_vehicles_by_type with vehicle_type set to "motos".

17. The agent must not call get_vehicles_by_type with vehicle_type set to "motorcycles".

18. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Toyota" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

19. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Honda" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

20. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Hyundai" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

21. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Fiat" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

22. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Chevrolet" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

23. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Jeep" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

24. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "BMW" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

25. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Audi" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

26. The agent must not call search_car_price with brand_name set to "Nissan" as it is a passenger-car-only brand.

27. The agent must not loop through all brands in the truck category to build a bulk pricing database.

28. The agent may only look up brands the analyst specifically names.

29. The agent must not present FIPE values as legally binding appraisals.

30. The agent must not present FIPE values as guaranteed resale values.

31. The agent must not calculate total cost of ownership for vehicles.

32. The agent must not calculate financing terms for vehicles.

33. The agent must not recommend specific purchase decisions.

34. The agent must not query more than 5 distinct brands in a single conversation turn without explicit analyst instruction.

35. When the analyst asks about a brand that manufactures both trucks and passenger cars, the agent should proceed with the lookup but clarify that search_car_price results show models from the FIPE car database.

36. When the analyst asks about a brand that manufactures both trucks and passenger cars, the agent should clarify that truck-specific models may require browsing the truck category via get_vehicles_by_type("caminhoes").

37. When the analyst asks to "check all truck prices," the agent should ask which specific brands to compare rather than enumerating the full list.

38. When the analyst requests motorcycle data, the agent should decline and explain that its scope is limited to commercial vehicle truck procurement research.

39. When the analyst requests passenger car data, the agent should decline and explain that its scope is limited to commercial vehicle truck procurement research.